SOP: Salesforce Lead Integration & Data Quality Governance
Version: 1.0
Owner: Ghulam Fatima

Objective: To ensure 100% data accuracy and zero duplication for all inbound Leads processed via the Python-Salesforce API pipeline.

1. Scope
This procedure applies to the automated ingestion of Lead data from external sources into the Salesforce CRM environment.

2. Roles & Responsibilities
Data Analyst (Me): Responsible for executing scripts, monitoring logs, and resolving validation flags.
System Admin: Responsible for managing API credentials and Salesforce Org permissions.

3. The "DATA" Framework (Standardized Process)
We follow the Define, Automate, Train, Audit framework to maintain high-quality records.


# Step 1: Pre-Ingestion Validation

Before data is sent to Salesforce, the utils/validator.py script must perform the following checks:
Email Syntax: Must match standard [email protected] format via Regex.
Name Integrity: LastName must contain at least 2 characters (prevents "N/A" or "test" entries).
Action: If a record fails, it is logged in the errors.log and blocked from entry to keep the CRM clean.

Step 2: Intelligent Deduplication (The "Upsert" Rule)
To prevent "inflated pipeline" reports, the system must check for existing records:
Query Salesforce via SOQL using the Email field as the Unique Identifier.
If Match Found: Perform a PATCH request to update existing fields.
If No Match: Perform a POST request to create a new record.

Step 3: Error Handling & Escalation
If the API returns a 401 (Unauthorized) or 403 (Forbidden) error:
Check the .env file for expired client_secret credentials.
Verify the Salesforce Connected App settings.
If unresolved within 30 minutes, escalate to the System Admin.

4. Continuous Improvement (Audit)
Monthly Health Check: Run a Salesforce report to identify records with "Incomplete Data" or "Inconsistent Casing".
Standardization: Ensure all company names follow a consistent format (e.g., "Company Inc." vs "Company").
